"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-12-six-new-sports-revealed-next-olympics-one-gets-scrapped-21405208\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"TheOlympicsinParismay have only just come to an end - but thoughts are already turning tothe next showpiece in the United Statesin 2028.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 136, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There were new sports and events introduced in France this year, including a first ever appearance for breaking.\", \"from\": 138, \"to\": 250, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 185, \"end\": 191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9352601779209694, \"rank\": 0.06699170044925437, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kayak cross made its Olympic debut as canoe slalom athletes raced directly against one another, rather than just the clock.\", \"from\": 252, \"to\": 375, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 252, \"end\": 257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayak\", \"score\": 0.9912583416421268, \"rank\": 0.008818748847372547, \"text\": \"Kayak\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayak\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayak\"}, {\"begin\": 296, \"end\": 302, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canoe_slalom\", \"score\": 0.9999918957042682, \"rank\": 8.104361592471613e-06, \"text\": \"slalom\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canoe_slalom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canoe_slalom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Out on the track and field,the repechage round was also used for the first timefor every short to middle distance racing event except the 100m sprint.\", \"from\": 377, \"to\": 527, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But how many new events will survive and what additions will there be when we do it all again in Los Angeles in 2028?\", \"from\": 529, \"to\": 646, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 626, \"end\": 637, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999980173016, \"rank\": 1.3337772683872316e-09, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One event has already been scrapped, with doubt lingering over another, and six new sports have been revealed for the next Games.\", \"from\": 648, \"to\": 777, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us take a look at what will change in LA.\", \"from\": 778, \"to\": 823, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Breaking made its Olympic debut in Paris and it's safe to sayits inclusion caused quite a stir.\", \"from\": 825, \"to\": 920, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 860, \"end\": 865, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 2.4589776287900934e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some fans were particularly unimpressed andAustralian breakdancer Raygun lashed out at the IOC and criticsafter her routine scored zero points and went viral.\", \"from\": 922, \"to\": 1080, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 988, \"end\": 994, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raygun\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5566677767936383e-28, \"text\": \"Raygun\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raygun\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raygun\"}, {\"begin\": 1013, \"end\": 1016, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.011254359212561e-38, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cycling legend Sir Chris Hoydefended the 'fantastic' eventbut Olympic chiefs revealed that breaking had already been scrapped for LA 2028 before it even came to a conclusion.\", \"from\": 1082, \"to\": 1256, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a bit of a flash in the pan and there will be no breaking at the next Olympics.\", \"from\": 1258, \"to\": 1344, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Boxing has not yet been confirmed for LA because of issues over the governing body for the sport at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1346, \"to\": 1459, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The competition was run by the IOC in Paris after it stripped the International Boxing Association (IBA) of recognition over allegations of corruption, including governance, finance, refereeing and ethical issues.\", \"from\": 1461, \"to\": 1674, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1492, \"end\": 1495, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.011254359212561e-38, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1499, \"end\": 1504, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 2.4589776287900934e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1527, \"end\": 1559, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8827001328944466e-20, \"text\": \"International Boxing Association\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 1561, \"end\": 1564, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.7966727082629624, \"rank\": 0.2534499729030903, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\", \"Q141683\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As yet, the IOC has not included boxing in the programme for 2028 and warned that if a new governing body cannot be found, the sport will not feature.\", \"from\": 1676, \"to\": 1826, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1688, \"end\": 1691, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.011254359212561e-38, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"IOC president Thomas Bach said a decision on boxing's inclusion needs to be made in 2025.\", \"from\": 1828, \"to\": 1917, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1828, \"end\": 1831, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.011254359212561e-38, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1842, \"end\": 1853, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomas Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only time will tell if boxing features in the US.\", \"from\": 1918, \"to\": 1967, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Six sports which did not feature in Paris will be included in Los Angeles - and two of those will be making an Olympic debut.\", \"from\": 1969, \"to\": 2094, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2005, \"end\": 2010, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 2.4589776287900934e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2031, \"end\": 2042, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999980173016, \"rank\": 1.3337772683872316e-09, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They are flag football and squash.\", \"from\": 2095, \"to\": 2129, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Flag football is a variant of American football whereby players must remove a flag or flag belt from the ball carrier to end a down, instead of tackling them to the ground.\", \"from\": 2131, \"to\": 2303, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Each team consists of five players and the game is played on a 50-yard field with no offensive linemen, according to the IOC.\", \"from\": 2305, \"to\": 2430, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2426, \"end\": 2429, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.011254359212561e-38, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Squash is a popular racket sport which can be played either as a singles or doubles match.\", \"from\": 2432, \"to\": 2522, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Players compete in a four-walled court and attempt to hit the ball onto the playable surfaces of the walls.\", \"from\": 2524, \"to\": 2631, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The aim of the game is to hit the ball in such a way that the opponent is unable to hit a legal return shot.\", \"from\": 2633, \"to\": 2741, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Both squash and flag football will be considered as 'optional' sports, meaning they may not return for Brisbane 2032.\", \"from\": 2743, \"to\": 2860, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There are four new sports returning to the Olympic Games in Los Angeles in 2032.\", \"from\": 2862, \"to\": 2942, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2922, \"end\": 2933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999980173016, \"rank\": 1.3337772683872316e-09, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They are:  There wasn't any baseball at Paris 2024, but unsurprisingly, it will be back for the Games in the USA.\", \"from\": 2943, \"to\": 3056, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3052, \"end\": 3055, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9987050085608337, \"rank\": 0.0012721312079508184, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Baseball was an optional sport until 1992 when it became permanent.\", \"from\": 3058, \"to\": 3125, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was then dropped after 2008 before being readded as optional for Tokyo 2020.\", \"from\": 3126, \"to\": 3205, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3194, \"end\": 3199, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9998265958688669, \"rank\": 0.00017343420528305987, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's in-and-out status should end for the next two Olympics with it also expected to feature at Brisbane 2032.\", \"from\": 3207, \"to\": 3317, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Softball featured at every Olympics from 1996 to 2008 but was dropped for London 2012 and Rio 2016.\", \"from\": 3319, \"to\": 3418, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3393, \"end\": 3404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.635784690581536e-14, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It made a comeback for Tokyo 2020 but was once again left out for Paris 2024.\", \"from\": 3420, \"to\": 3497, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3443, \"end\": 3448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9998265958688669, \"rank\": 0.00017343420528305987, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3486, \"end\": 3496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.466112515246938e-38, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It returns as an optional sport in LA 2028.\", \"from\": 3498, \"to\": 3541, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lacrosse will feature at the Olympics in LA for the first time in 120 years, having last been contested in 1908.\", \"from\": 3543, \"to\": 3655, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3543, \"end\": 3551, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lacrosse\", \"score\": 0.9999999999672582, \"rank\": 1.7631